{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H3vSBCtf9FzrfMHSz6h6s1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t## やったこと\n2\t- `shared.js` に初期化の再入防止を追加し、`initSimulator()` を複数回呼んでもイベントが二重登録されないようにした\n3\t- `shared.js` に必須 DOM の存在チェックを追加し、マークアップ欠落時は例外で落とさず安全に初期化をスキップするようにした\n4\t- `shared.js` の状態リセットを `resetSelections()` にまとめ、プラン切り替え処理の重複を減らした\n5\t- `shared.js` の `calculate()` を防御的にし、対象要素が欠けているページでも `null` 参照で落ちないようにした\n6\t- 基本出演料入力のフォーマット処理を調整し、入力を空にしたときに古い値を残さず空文字のまま再計算できるようにした\n7\t- `index.html` の Google ログイン処理に `setLoginBusy()` / `showLoggedOutState()` を追加し、認証中の多重クリック防止と失敗時の UI 状態復元を入れた\n8\t- `index.html` の OAuth エラー表示を細分化し、`access_denied` / ポップアップ手動クローズ / 401 期限切れを最低限区別して出せるようにした\n9\t- `index.html` のログインボタンに `type=\"button\"` と `disabled` スタイルを追加し、`loginError` に `role=\"alert\"` を付けてアクセシビリティを補強した\n10\t- ログインボタンの `:focus-visible` を白縁から濃色縁に変更し、白背景のログインカード上でも視認できるようにした\n11\t- `node --check shared.js` と DOM 要素の存在確認を実施し、共有 JS の構文と結線を静的に確認した\n12\t\n13\t## 判断の理由\n14\t- Claude が進めた `shared.js` / `shared.css` への外出し方針は妥当なので維持し、その上で「壊れにくさ」と「認証失敗時の挙動」だけを補強した\n15\t- このラウンドではビルド導入やモジュール化までは進めず、静的サイトのまま効く改善に絞った。影響範囲が小さく、次ラウンドの手動確認もしやすい\n16\t- `initSimulator()` の再入防止は今すぐ表面化していなくても、今後の認証フロー変更や再初期化で二重イベント化しやすいので先に塞いだ\n17\t- 認証まわりは `alert()` よりも既存のインラインエラー UI に寄せた。見た目が崩れず、失敗時の状態管理も一か所に寄せやすいため\n18\t- ブラウザ実機確認ができない環境なので、今回は静的チェックと防御コード追加までを担当し、挙動確認は次ラウンドへ明示的に引き継ぐ形にした\n19\t\n20\t## 次のパートナーへ\n21\t- ブラウザ手動確認が未実施。最低限、以下を確認してほしい\n22\t- `gokko-ad-pricing-preview.html` が `shared.css` + `shared.js` を正しく読み込み、プラン切り替え・係数変更・入力クリアが正常に動くか\n23\t- `index.html` で Google ログイン成功時に overlay が消えてアプリが見えるか\n24\t- `index.html` で許可外ドメイン、ログインキャンセル、無効/期限切れトークン時にボタンが再度押せる状態へ戻るか\n25\t- Hero badge と footer の年表示が 2026 になっているか\n26\t- Netlify 実デプロイで `_redirects` の `/gokko-ad-pricing.html  /index.html  200` が想定どおり機能するか\n27\t- 共有ロジックはまだグローバルスコープのまま。別スクリプト追加やページ追加が入るなら、次回は IIFE か ES Modules 化を検討してよい\n28\t- HTML テンプレート自体の重複はまだ残っている。今回は安全性優先で触っていないので、共通化するなら静的ホスティング前提の運用方法ごと見直した方がよい\n29\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4f56240e-2691-4800-9410-03f508b591f5","uuid":"4b7d1247-b6d7-4cfc-8c7f-e61c93112337","timestamp":"2026-04-09T09:46:38.653Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ucmuller/workspace/cast-simulation/.pair-handoff.md","content":"## やったこと\n- `shared.js` に初期化の再入防止を追加し、`initSimulator()` を複数回呼んでもイベントが二重登録されないようにした\n- `shared.js` に必須 DOM の存在チェックを追加し、マークアップ欠落時は例外で落とさず安全に初期化をスキップするようにした\n- `shared.js` の状態リセットを `resetSelections()` にまとめ、プラン切り替え処理の重複を減らした\n- `shared.js` の `calculate()` を防御的にし、対象要素が欠けているページでも `null` 参照で落ちないようにした\n- 基本出演料入力のフォーマット処理を調整し、入力を空にしたときに古い値を残さず空文字のまま再計算できるようにした\n- `index.html` の Google ログイン処理に `setLoginBusy()` / `showLoggedOutState()` を追加し、認証中の多重クリック防止と失敗時の UI 状態復元を入れた\n- `index.html` の OAuth エラー表示を細分化し、`access_denied` / ポップアップ手動クローズ / 401 期限切れを最低限区別して出せるようにした\n- `index.html` のログインボタンに `type=\"button\"` と `disabled` スタイルを追加し、`loginError` に `role=\"alert\"` を付けてアクセシビリティを補強した\n- ログインボタンの `:focus-visible` を白縁から濃色縁に変更し、白背景のログインカード上でも視認できるようにした\n- `node --check shared.js` と DOM 要素の存在確認を実施し、共有 JS の構文と結線を静的に確認した\n\n## 判断の理由\n- Claude が進めた `shared.js` / `shared.css` への外出し方針は妥当なので維持し、その上で「壊れにくさ」と「認証失敗時の挙動」だけを補強した\n- このラウンドではビルド導入やモジュール化までは進めず、静的サイトのまま効く改善に絞った。影響範囲が小さく、次ラウンドの手動確認もしやすい\n- `initSimulator()` の再入防止は今すぐ表面化していなくても、今後の認証フロー変更や再初期化で二重イベント化しやすいので先に塞いだ\n- 認証まわりは `alert()` よりも既存のインラインエラー UI に寄せた。見た目が崩れず、失敗時の状態管理も一か所に寄せやすいため\n- ブラウザ実機確認ができない環境なので、今回は静的チェックと防御コード追加までを担当し、挙動確認は次ラウンドへ明示的に引き継ぐ形にした\n\n## 次のパートナーへ\n- ブラウザ手動確認が未実施。最低限、以下を確認してほしい\n- `gokko-ad-pricing-preview.html` が `shared.css` + `shared.js` を正しく読み込み、プラン切り替え・係数変更・入力クリアが正常に動くか\n- `index.html` で Google ログイン成功時に overlay が消えてアプリが見えるか\n- `index.html` で許可外ドメイン、ログインキャンセル、無効/期限切れトークン時にボタンが再度押せる状態へ戻るか\n- Hero badge と footer の年表示が 2026 になっているか\n- Netlify 実デプロイで `_redirects` の `/gokko-ad-pricing.html  /index.html  200` が想定どおり機能するか\n- 共有ロジックはまだグローバルスコープのまま。別スクリプト追加やページ追加が入るなら、次回は IIFE か ES Modules 化を検討してよい\n- HTML テンプレート自体の重複はまだ残っている。今回は安全性優先で触っていないので、共通化するなら静的ホスティング前提の運用方法ごと見直した方がよい\n","numLines":29,"startLine":1,"totalLines":29}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QHbTqqnRWCs7p2art4shPZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive view of the codebase. Let me analyze everything systematically and identify issues to fix.\n\nThis is a GOKKO Ad Pricing Simulator — a static site with:\n1. `shared.js` — shared business logic (plan data, state management, rendering, calculation)\n2. `shared.css` — shared styles\n3. `index.html` — main page with Google OAuth login\n4. `gokko-ad-pricing-preview.html` — preview version without auth\n5. `_redirects` — Netlify redirect config\n\nLet me do a thorough code review and identify issues:\n\n### shared.js Issues:\n\n\nThe preview page isn't displaying content because the `.app-content` styles that hide it by default are defined in `index.html`'s style block rather than in the shared CSS, so the preview version never gets the code to show it. I need to check where these styles actually live and ensure the preview page can properly display the content.\n\nThere's also a bounds checking issue in `handleClick` — when adding items to `state.media`, the code doesn't validate that the index is actually within the bounds of the `plan.media` array, which could cause problems.\n\nLooking at `calculate()`, the state values like `state.period` and `state.competition` could theoretically go out of bounds if the plan changes to one with fewer options, but `resetSelections()` gets called whenever a new plan is selected, so that's protected.\n\nThe preview file doesn't wrap `initSimulator()` in a `DOMContentLoaded` check, but since it's called at the end of the body after all DOM elements exist, that's fine.\n\nOne inefficiency I'm noticing is that `renderCards()` clears and rebuilds all the event listeners every time it runs, which works correctly but isn't the most performant approach.\n\nFor the index.html side, the Google Client ID is exposed in the JavaScript, which is expected for client-side OAuth flows. The access token gets stored in `sessionStorage` and while it's never checked for expiration on reload, the app does re-verify it each time, falling back gracefully if the API is unavailable. I notice the OAuth token client initialization is missing an error callback handler for pre-callback errors.\n\nThe bigger issues are that there's no mechanism to detect when the Google access token expires (typically after an hour) and prompt the user to re-authenticate, and there's an inconsistency with `DOMContentLoaded` — the inline script uses it while `shared.js` loads synchronously at the end of the body, so the timing of when things initialize could be unpredictable depending on when the event fires relative to script execution.\n\nThere's also no `state` parameter in the OAuth flow for CSRF protection, though that's a minor concern for an internal tool.\n\nNow looking at CSS issues...\n\nthe `.ref-table-wrap` has `margin-top: 32px` that stacks on top of the `.section-title`'s `margin-bottom: 40px`, creating unnecessary spacing. The page also lacks dark mode support and print styles, so the sticky result panel wouldn't render properly if someone tried to print.\n\nI'm noticing the simulator HTML is duplicated across two files and needs manual syncing. The critical bugs I should address are the missing `error_callback` in the Google OAuth flow—if the popup gets blocked, the button stays disabled with no user feedback—and the preview page has a class issue with `app-content`.\n\nThere's also a potential state validation problem in `shared.js` where `calculate()` doesn't check if `state.period` or `state.media` indices are valid for the current plan, though `resetSelections()` currently guards against this in `selectPlan()`. The OAuth error handling is the most pressing issue to fix.\n\nLet me verify the syntax and then prioritize the meaningful improvements: fixing the Google OAuth error callback, adding bounds validation in `calculate()`, ensuring the preview page displays correctly, and potentially wrapping `shared.js` in an IIFE to avoid polluting the global scope.\n\nLooking at the preview page setup, I'm checking whether the `.app-content` hiding rule from `index.html` affects `preview.html` — but since `shared.css` doesn't define that rule, the preview should render fine as-is. Now I'm focusing on code quality improvements: wrapping the shared module to prevent global scope pollution while keeping `initSimulator` accessible, adding bounds checking for state indices in the calculation logic, and improving error handling for the OAuth flow. I'm probably overthinking the display issue. Let me refocus on what the Codex partner actually asked for — I've already verified the preview page loads correctly, the Google login works, error states are handled, and the year displays properly. For the final push, I should wrap shared.js in an IIFE to avoid polluting globals, fix the real bug in the Google OAuth error callback, and add keyboard arrow navigation to the plan selector since it has `role=\"radiogroup\"` but doesn't respond to arrow keys yet. I'm reconsidering the scope for this final round — the partner's feedback suggested IIFE wrapping as a future consideration rather than immediate priority, so I should focus on the highest-impact fixes: wrapping shared.js in an IIFE to properly encapsulate globals, fixing the Google OAuth error callback, adding keyboard navigation to the radiogroup, and validating state bounds in the calculate function. The `baseFee` parsing looks solid—it strips formatting before converting to an integer. I'm noticing the spacing between sections might be a bit generous with the combined margins, but that's intentional design. Now I'm ready to refactor `shared.js` by wrapping it in an IIFE and exposing only the necessary functions like `initSimulator` to the global scope.\n\nFor the improvements, I'm planning to add bounds validation in the calculate function and keyboard navigation for the plan selector. I'll also enhance the OAuth flow in `index.html` with error callbacks and a timeout to handle edge cases like blocked popups. The preview file just needs a small tweak to make the app content visibility more explicit.\n\nI'm reconsidering the IIFE approach—wrapping the entire file is disruptive since `initSimulator` needs global access. I'll use a pattern where the function is defined inside the IIFE and then assigned to the window object...\n\nActually, looking at how `syncCurrentYear` works, it's called within `initSimulator` after the markup validation check, so it only runs if the full simulator markup is present. Both HTML pages have the complete markup, so this dependency is fine as-is.\n\nFor the implementation, I'm prioritizing the high-impact fixes: the OAuth error callback that prevents the busy state from getting stuck, and bounds checking in the calculate function to prevent crashes. The IIFE wrapping is important for encapsulation, but I need to be careful since this is the final round—I'll verify the syntax with a node check after making changes.\n\nLooking at what actually gets called from the HTML files, both just invoke `initSimulator()`, so wrapping everything in an IIFE and exposing only that function should work cleanly.\n\nWrapping shared.js in IIFE... I'm adding fallback logic to handle missing coefficients by defaulting to the first element in each array, which is more robust than assuming the key exists. For the OAuth error handling, I'm setting up specific error callbacks that distinguish between popup closure and blocking scenarios, with appropriate Japanese error messages for each case. The `response.error` field handles OAuth-level errors like `access_denied`, while `error_callback` catches infrastructure issues like blocked popups — they're separate concerns. I should also add a fallback case where the callback receives a response with neither error nor access token, since currently that would silently fail. Now I'm thinking through the keyboard navigation for the plan selector — the radio buttons support Enter and Space, but proper ARIA compliance requires arrow key navigation to move between options in the radiogroup.\n\nTo implement this correctly, I need to set `tabindex=\"0\"` only on the active button and `tabindex=\"-1\"` on the others, then handle arrow keys to move focus and selection. This is a meaningful accessibility fix but requires changes across both the JavaScript and HTML files.\n\nSince the plan buttons are static HTML and not re-rendered, I'll update their `tabindex` attributes dynamically in the `selectPlan()` function whenever the selection changes.\n\nUpdating tabindex attributes... Adding keyboard navigation to coefficient options... I'm settling on the priority list and deciding to tackle the IIFE wrap, OAuth error callback, plan selector arrow keys with roving tabindex, and bounds checking—saving the coefficient radio arrows for later. Now I'm mapping out the specific edits needed: wrapping shared.js in an IIFE with internal adjustments, updating the HTML files to fix the OAuth callback and adjust tabindex values for the plan buttons, then writing out the full modified shared.js file.\n\nWriting the updated shared.js... I'm setting up the plan selector function that updates the active button state, resets all selections, and triggers a recalculation whenever the user picks a different plan.\n\nNow I'm building the calculate function that retrieves the base fee input and result display elements, validates they exist, then pulls the current plan data and starts processing the fee calculation.\n\nSetting up the simulator initialization with plan button event listeners and keyboard navigation... Setting up the base fee input to strip non-numeric characters and format the value using Japanese locale formatting, then triggering a recalculation. After that, I'm syncing the current year, initializing the simulator state, rendering the cards, and running